            "title": "How to foster prosocial behavior? : essays on experimental economics",
            "abstract": [
                "The starting point of this dissertation is the idea that it is in the interest of society to foster prosocial behavior. Far more debatable is which strategies are suitable to promote prosocial behavior. In this thesis, I consider three measures: the implementation of a reputation system, asking agents directly to act prosocially, and a taking frame. I run laboratory experiments that are designed to deepen the understanding of the impact of these three strategies. In Study 1, which is joint work with Claudia Keser, we analyze if the fostering impact of reputation systems on prosocial behavio...",
